sudo apt-get remove --auto-remove nameOFprogram

sudo apt-get purge --auto-remove nameOFprogram






example


Uninstall mailutils
To remove just mailutils package itself from Ubuntu 14.10 (Utopic Unicorn) execute on terminal:

sudo apt-get remove mailutils
Uninstall mailutils and it's dependent packages
To remove the mailutils package and any other dependant package which are no longer needed from Ubuntu Utopic.

sudo apt-get remove --auto-remove mailutils
Purging mailutils
If you also want to delete configuration and/or data files of mailutils from Ubuntu Utopic then this will work:

sudo apt-get purge mailutils
To delete configuration and/or data files of mailutils and it's dependencies from Ubuntu Utopic then execute:

sudo apt-get purge --auto-remove mailutils
